The article is a proclamation by President Donald Trump declaring April 14, 2017, as Pan American Day and April 9 through April 15, 2017, as Pan American Week. The proclamation commemorates the 127th anniversary of the conclusion of the First International Conference of American States, which led to the creation of the Organization of American States. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of strengthening relationships with regional partners and promoting democracy, security, human rights, and economic development in the Americas. President Trump also highlights his administration's commitment to improving border security, combating terrorism, and dismantling transnational criminal networks. The proclamation calls upon the people of the United States to observe the day with appropriate ceremonies and activities.